<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,775,465,552]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,276,465,489]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis. –</emphasis>
Paramere narrowed distally, slightly hooked apically (
<figureCitation box="[238,346,497,520]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[136,181,2037,2058]" captionTargetBox="[144,1452,984,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-130@2.[109,1481,963,2004]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 3-6. Stegana (Oxyphortica) aotsukai, new species, male genitalia: 3. epandrium (epand) and cercus (cerc); 4. surstylus; 5. hypandrium (hypd), paramere (pm), gonopod (gon), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 6. ditto (lateral view) (scale-line = 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618899/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Figs. 5, 6</figureCitation>
); aedeagus with 1 curved, lobe-shaped process basally (
<figureCitation box="[317,383,529,552]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[136,181,2037,2058]" captionTargetBox="[144,1452,984,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-130@2.[109,1481,963,2004]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 3-6. Stegana (Oxyphortica) aotsukai, new species, male genitalia: 3. epandrium (epand) and cercus (cerc); 4. surstylus; 5. hypandrium (hypd), paramere (pm), gonopod (gon), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 6. ditto (lateral view) (scale-line = 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618899/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="32" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,775,593,776]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,295,593,617]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Description. –</emphasis>
Thorax: Mesonotum yellow, with 3 black, longitudinal stripes per side: submedial and later stripes extend to prescutum; sublateral stripes short between scutal and scutellar sulci. Pleura yellow mostly, with 1 black, longitudinal stripe medially. Scutellum medially black, laterally yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,584,817,840]" box="[136,584,817,840]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Wing: Dark brown. Halter greyish black.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,775,881,936]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Legs: Mid tibia basally with 2 long, strong postero-dorsal setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[835,1470,193,312]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Abdomen: Second to fourth tergites yellow to dark yellow on anterior margin, with laterally and medially protruded, black band on posterior margin; fifth and sixth nearly entirely black. Sternites yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[835,1470,353,504]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">
Male terminalia: Epandrium not constricted mid-dorsally, with 1 row of long, strong setae and 2 rows of short setae along posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1092,1156,417,440]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[136,181,2037,2058]" captionTargetBox="[144,1452,984,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-130@2.[109,1481,963,2004]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 3-6. Stegana (Oxyphortica) aotsukai, new species, male genitalia: 3. epandrium (epand) and cercus (cerc); 4. surstylus; 5. hypandrium (hypd), paramere (pm), gonopod (gon), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 6. ditto (lateral view) (scale-line = 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618899/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Surstylus with several setae on distal margin, and 1 hole near posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1390,1457,449,472]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[136,181,2037,2058]" captionTargetBox="[144,1452,984,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-130@2.[109,1481,963,2004]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 3-6. Stegana (Oxyphortica) aotsukai, new species, male genitalia: 3. epandrium (epand) and cercus (cerc); 4. surstylus; 5. hypandrium (hypd), paramere (pm), gonopod (gon), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 6. ditto (lateral view) (scale-line = 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618899/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus apically bifurcate (
<figureCitation box="[1154,1219,481,504]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[136,181,2037,2058]" captionTargetBox="[144,1452,984,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-130@2.[109,1481,963,2004]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 3-6. Stegana (Oxyphortica) aotsukai, new species, male genitalia: 3. epandrium (epand) and cercus (cerc); 4. surstylus; 5. hypandrium (hypd), paramere (pm), gonopod (gon), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral view); 6. ditto (lateral view) (scale-line = 0.1 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4618899" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4618899/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[835,1471,545,728]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31">For morphological terminology and index definitions, see Chen &amp; Toda (2001) or Chen &amp; Aotsuka (2003).</paragraph>
