<emphasis box="[566,688,545,568]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="32">nigripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the many characters, but can be clearly distinguished from the latter by paramere distally narrowed and aedeagus basally with 1 curved process (paramere distally broad and aedeagus basally without curved process in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[485,608,673,696]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripennis">
